text: Wenren Yuntao (born 27 February 1994) is a Chinese taekwondo practitioner. She won a bronze medal in flyweight at the 2017 World Taekwondo Championships, after being defeated by Panipak Wongpattanakit in the semifinal. She competed in bantamweight at the 2019 World Taekwondo Championships, where she was defeated by eventual gold medalist Phannapa Harnsujin in the 1/8-finals. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Chinese female taekwondo practitioners Category:Taekwondo practitioners at the 2018 Asian Games Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists
